               <p>URIAH DAVIS. I lodge in Holborn. On the 22d of November I was informed that I had lost something while I was passing <placeName id="t18241202-32-crimeloc171">Red Lion-passage</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-32-crimeloc171" type="placeName" value="Red Lion-passage"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18241202-32-crimeloc171" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241202-32-off169 t18241202-32-crimeloc171"></join>. I felt in my pocket and missed my handkerchief, which was safe about two hours and a half before; I saw it in the hands of the person who stopped the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-32-person256">
                  JAMES 
                  WILDE
               <interp inst="t18241202-32-person256" type="surname" value="WILDE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person256" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner on the evening of the 22d of November, walking behind Mr. Davis and another young man. The prisoner made several attempts at the pocket, and at last he got the handkerchief out. I ran and took hold of him; as I was taking him to the watch-house several persons came round me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-32-person257">
                  WILLIAM 
                  FRUNING
               <interp inst="t18241202-32-person257" type="surname" value="FRUNING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person257" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I saw the prisoner running, and Wilde pursuing him. I went to the watch-house, and took charge of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18241202-32-person258">
                  FREDERICK 
                  COOK
               <interp inst="t18241202-32-person258" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person258" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18241202-32-person258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner attempt to take the handkerchief out of Mr. Davis's pocket. I cried Stop thief! and saw him taken.</p>
